translated: Johnsson, John Olof, office manager, Gothenburg, born September 11, 1886 in Asarum, Blekinge county, son of John J. and Carolina Möller. Married in 1940 to Vivan Johnsson. He graduated from Mog: ex in 1905 and received a law degree from Lund University in 1910. He served as a court clerk in Askims district from 1910-1912, then was appointed deputy notary and acting prosecutor in the Svea Court of Appeal from 1912-1917. He served as a notary on the parliamentary committee of witnesses in 1914 and 1915, assistant in the Gothenburg Land Survey Board in 1917, acting director of real estate in 1918, legal deputy in the Gothenburg City Council Secretariat in 1922, city council secretary since 1926, and office manager of Gothenburg City College since 1932. He was a member of the board of directors for Gothenburg Legal Aid Society and Fredrik Mossherg's pharmacy fund, secretary of the board for Otof and Caroline Wijk's foundation, and served on the board of the Present and Gothenburg Housing Credit Association. He was awarded the Order of the North Star and the Order of Vasa.
